{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Plan-review fidelity-eval: add G3/G4 to the eval suite (reuse existing infra; non-blocking)\n\n## Why\nS4 (merge G3+G4) and S5 (bin-packing) need a SEMANTIC check (real findings: new container path vs baseline).\nrebar ALREADY has the eval infra — do NOT build a new harness:\n- the Inspect-AI / promptfoo EVAL SEAM (workflow WS-G);\n- the per-criterion plan-review eval suite `src/rebar/llm/eval_specs/*.eval.yaml` (built under epic 5fd2);\n- `src/rebar/llm/parity.py` parallel-run-and-diff (recall + false-accept on a gold set, `min_gold` floor).\nThe container criteria G3/G4 are NOT covered by any eval spec today — a real gap. This story FILLS it and plugs\ninto epic 6f2d (soupy-spool-revel) WS-EVAL-EXISTING's standing parallel-run-and-diff discipline (relates_to 6f2d).\n\n## What\n- Add G3/G4 (container) eval specs (e.g. `eval_specs/plan-review-container.eval.yaml`) with discrimination/recall\n  fixtures over the shared corpuses (DSO read-only / snap-oakhart / rebar's own tickets), mirroring the existing specs.\n- Reuse `parity.py` (recall / false-accept, `min_gold`) as the \"merged-vs-separate\" (S4) and \"packed-vs-per-child\"\n  (S5) diff. Baseline = current separate-call (G3,G4)/one-child-per-call findings; candidate = merged/packed.\n- Metric = finding recall + G3/G4 attribution accuracy; explicit, documented tolerance.\n\n## CI posture (cautious: evals are non-deterministic + cost live $)\n- The OFFLINE discipline check (spec validity + grader discipline; deterministic, no model) runs on every PR and\n  is a REQUIRED check today — the new G3/G4 specs simply join it (cheap, safe to block).\n- The LIVE semantic eval (billable, non-deterministic) stays OPT-IN — `workflow_dispatch`, optionally PATH-SCOPED\n  to `reviewers/**` + `eval_specs/**` + `plan_review/**` so it never runs on irrelevant changes — and is NEVER a\n  required/blocking CI status check.\n- For S4/S5 the live eval is a HUMAN-REVIEWED DEVELOPMENT GATE (run it, review recall/attribution, pass before\n  merge), NOT a CI blocker — a flaky run can't block the build and it costs nothing on unrelated PRs.\n\n## Scope\n- In: G3/G4 eval specs in the existing suite; reuse of parity.py + the Inspect seam; the candidate-vs-baseline\n  metric/tolerance; the CI-posture wiring (offline discipline validates the new specs; live eval gated/path-scoped/\n  non-blocking).\n- Out: the merge (S4) / bin-pack (S5) implementations it gates.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] G3/G4 container eval specs are added to `src/rebar/llm/eval_specs` and pass the OFFLINE discipline check\n      (deterministic, runs on every PR).\n- [ ] The eval reuses `parity.py` (recall + false-accept, `min_gold`) to diff a candidate container path vs the\n      baseline, reporting finding-recall + G3/G4-attribution accuracy.\n- [ ] An explicit numeric tolerance is defined + documented.\n- [ ] The LIVE semantic eval is OPT-IN (workflow_dispatch / path-scoped) and NON-BLOCKING — NOT a required CI\n      status check; documented as a human-reviewed development gate for S4/S5.\n- [ ] No new live LLM cost is incurred on PRs that do not touch plan-review/reviewer/eval_specs.\n- [ ] `make lint` + tests pass.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782562198466910001,"uuid":"70fd003d-68b2-4194-8b15-c4a82d60a5de"}